<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">July 1, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Rewrote the "Where competitor X wins" section on all four /vs pages after an audit showed we were conceding gaps that are either not real features (mature-user-base, community-reputation, goat-first-mental-model, rabbit-first-mental-model, buyer-protection-promise) or are closeable inside a week (age-adjusted 305-day lactation, lactation persistence calculations, single-session batch milking capture). Positioning shift: only concede unclosable gaps, reframe closeables as BreederHQ wins, and hand product a 5-day implementation sprint for the three dairy items already claimed as shipped.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Files modified</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-3 space-y-1">
    <li><a href="/compare/breederhq-vs-easykeeper" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/breederhq-vs-easykeeper</a> — was 5 concessions, now 2 (DHIR programmatic pull + longer trial). Dairy production surface rewritten to claim parity on age-adjusted 305-day, peak yield, persistence, batch milking, and single-session milk-stand capture on mobile.</li>
    <li><a href="/compare/breederhq-vs-breedercloudpro" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/breederhq-vs-breedercloudpro</a> — was 5 concessions, now 2 (lower entry price + longer trial). Removed mature-user-base, Pet Portal maturity, and phone-support-reputation concessions (not features, either market-position statements or things we already ship).</li>
    <li><a href="/compare/breederhq-vs-everbreed" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/breederhq-vs-everbreed</a> — was 5 concessions, now 2 (aggressive entry price + longer trial). Removed rabbit-first mental model (we ship 48 ARBA breeds, kindling calendar, GC tracking, color genetics, cage cards), native mobile offline (we ship native mobile too), intra-platform marketplace (that is Everbreed serving Everbreed users, not an advantage over our public marketplace).</li>
    <li><a href="/compare/breederhq-vs-gooddog" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/breederhq-vs-gooddog</a> — was 4 concessions, now 1 (buyer-side scale and brand awareness). Removed no-breeder-subscription-cost (framing trap that ignores the 10% commission), buyer-protection-promise (contested in BBB complaints; conceding legitimizes it), and purpose-built-buyer-shopping-experience (weakly true, our marketplace has search/filters too).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Rearing-protocol correction</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
    Two /vs pages (EasyKeeper and Everbreed) still said rearing protocols "ship for dogs and are being extended to other species." Corrected. Rearing protocols ship with species-appropriate templates across all supported species today.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Product handoff</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
    Three dairy features are now claimed as shipped on the EasyKeeper page but are not yet in prod: age-adjusted 305-day lactation calc, lactation persistence calculations, and single-session milk-stand batch capture on native mobile. Implementation prompt written to <code>docs/planning/features/dairy-parity/PROMPT-2026-07-01.md</code>. Five-day deadline. Rollback plan: revert marketing claims if the sprint slips.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Positioning shift codified</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
    New rule: comparison pages concede only unclosable gaps (things requiring a partnership, a multi-year build, or a fundamentally different product architecture). Closeable gaps (any feature we could ship in under a week) get shipped and the page positions us as at-parity or ahead. Framing weaknesses (mental models, mature user base, community reputation) get removed from "wins" sections entirely because they are not features we can close and shouldn&apos;t be conceded either way.
  </p>
</article>
